BANDAR SERI BEGAWAN, Jan. 8 (Xinhua) -- Brunei reported 20 new cases of COVID-19 on Saturday, bringing the country's total tally to 15,597. According to Brunei's Ministry of Health, the newly recorded cases included 15 local infections and five imported cases. As of Jan. 7 this year, 94.6 percent of Brunei's population had received at least one dose of the COVID-19 vaccines, while 93.6 percent had completed their vaccination schedule of two doses and 26.8 percent had received a booster shot. A total of 145 active cases are still being treated and monitored in Brunei, and 102 patients have died due to the coronavirus so far in the country.  â– 